    "John Trapp": "Ver. 25. { See Trapp on \"Mt 24:29\" }\nVer. 25. {See Trapp on \"Mt 24:29\"}",
    "Rudolf Schnackenburg, Sharon Pace": "From there Matthew goes on to recount the history of Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]`' passion\nand resurrection.\nThe discourse in\naddresses \"the crowds and his disciples\" (23:1), bears the special\nsignature of the evangelist. True, he applies material from the\nsources he has been consulting, Mark and the Sayings Source - more\n[v_Mrk_12_38] [v_Mrk_12_39] [v_Mrk_12_40] precisely, the brief address of Mark 12:38-40 (cf. Luke 20:45-47)\nand the lengthier woe discourse against the Pharisees and scribes\n[v_Luk_11_42] [v_Luk_11_43] [v_Luk_11_44] [v_Luk_11_45] [v_Luk_11_46] [v_Luk_11_47] [v_Luk_11_48] [v_Luk_11_49] [v_Luk_11_50] [v_Luk_11_51] [v_Luk_11_52] originating in Q and presented in Luke 11:42-"
